An account officer, Thadius, 37, on Thursday appeared before an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court, for allegedly stealing N1.4million and setting office ablaze. Thadius, whose house address was not provided, was charged with arson, a threat to damage, stealing and attempted arson, to which he pleaded not guilty. The prosecutor, Sergeant Felicia Okwori told the court that the defendant committed the offences on September 25 at Sweet Sensation Office located at Olowora, Ojudu Berger, Lagos State. READ ALSO: UK police search properties after 39 found dead in truck According to the prosecutor, Thadius stole the N1.4 million belonging to Sweet sensation Fast Food, thereafter set the financial controller’s office ablaze. She said that the offences contravened the provisions of Sections 343, 342, 344 and 287 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. News Agency of Nigeria reports that arson provides life imprisonment for the convict. Chief Magistrate G.O. Anifowoshe admitted the defendant to bail in the sum of N100, 000 bails with two sureties in like sum. Anifowoshe ordered that the sureties must be gainfully employed, with evidence of two years tax payment to the Lagos State Government. She adjourned the case until November 20 for hearing. (NAN)